20/04/2010
PRISTINA, Kosovo -- NATO officials announced on Monday (April 19th) that KFOR will transfer its duties related to securing the border with Albania to the Kosovo Police next week.
"I think the transfer ...
will happen on April 28th," KFOR Commander Markus Bentler said.
The NATO Commander of Allied Joint Force Command Naples, Admiral Mark Fitzgerald, who is visiting Kosovo, described it as a positive sign.
For the time being, there are no plans to transfer responsibility for the borders with Montenegro and Serbia.
(Kosova Sot, Express, Koha Ditore - 20/04/10)
